theorem Topology.denseInterior_of_dense_and_P1
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Dense A → Topology.P1 A → Dense (interior A) := by
  intro hDense hP1
  -- `A` is dense, so its closure is the whole space.
  have h_closureA : closure (A : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) := hDense.closure_eq
  -- From `P1`, `A ⊆ closure (interior A)`.
  have h_subset : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior A) := hP1
  -- Taking closures of both sides yields `closure A ⊆ closure (interior A)`.
  have h_closure_subset : (closure A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior A) := by
    have : (closure A : Set X) ⊆ closure (closure (interior A)) :=
      closure_mono h_subset
    simpa [closure_closure] using this
  -- Hence `univ ⊆ closure (interior A)`.
  have h_univ_subset : (Set.univ : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior A) := by
    simpa [h_closureA] using h_closure_subset
  -- The reverse inclusion is trivial.
  have h_subset_univ : closure (interior A) ⊆ (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    intro x hx; trivial
  -- Combine the inclusions to get the desired equality.
  have h_eq : closure (interior A) = (Set.univ : Set X) :=
    Set.Subset.antisymm h_univ_subset h_subset_univ
  -- Conclude that `interior A` is dense.
  simpa [Dense] using h_eq

theorem Topology.P2_of_denseInterior'
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hDense : Dense (interior A)) : Topology.P2 A := by
  dsimp [Topology.P2]
  intro x hxA
  -- The closure of `interior A` is the whole space.
  have h_closure : closure (interior A) = (Set.univ : Set X) := hDense.closure_eq
  -- Hence its interior is also the whole space.
  have : (x : X) ∈ interior (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    simpa [interior_univ]
  simpa [h_closure] using this
